  <span id="freeText1149182632451858938" style="display:none">I've read it in English...<br />A great dramatic story touches your soul moving some feelings, a struggle between the goodness and the evil, showing the angelic and the evil side inside some characters, rebelling their fates.<br />Ezzat, the main character found himself at the end of his life living a miserable life after trying to go beyond the borders, after rebelling the happy life with a great mother, a mother for all indeed..<br />He lost himself searching for love, Love often kills!<br />...<br />Although I read it in English, it didn't lose its charm, I felt it was originally written in English! <br /></span>
